gomodel:SYNGO_4156  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3C, D, E. Using electron microscopy and antibody-mediated staining, GluK2/3 was detected at mossy fibre-granule cell (MF-GC) synapses in WT mice. The antibody used is specific, as the immunofluorescence signal disappears in slices of GluK2.A1c knock-in mice (Figure 1C, Figure 1D).\n\nIntegral component of postsynaptic membrane is chosen based on current knowledge of GluK receptors being transmembrane receptors as indicated in P39087 (GRIK2_MOUSE).. Experimental description: \"GluK2.A1cyto knockin mice was generated with standard procedures using homologous recombinations of embryonic stem cells\". \"Horizontal slices from the ventral hippocampus (350 μm) were prepared from mice aged P19-P27 as previously described\"" , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2345-393X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9888-0928" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4156" ;
